A credit policy is given to a customer/client in order to allow them to acquire the product or services while being able to pay at a later date. For this problem, we will determine which of the credit policies will be better for the company by solving and comparing the net present value of the two policies. 

The net present value can be solved by using this formula:

$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Net present value}&=\text{Variable costs}+\dfrac{\text{Average daily sales}-\text{Total costs}}{\text{Interest rate}}
\end{aligned}$$
